Program: Start the Week
Title: Mohsin Hamid talks about How to Get Filthy Rich in Rising Asia
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01rfz5q
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 25 Mar 2013
On Start the Week Allan Little talks to Pakistani novelist, Mohsin Hamid about 'how to get filthy rich in rising Asia', and his self-help manual of rags to riches. The playwright Bruce Norris dramatises an entrepreneur's quest for wealth with priceless ambition, while Katherine Boo explores the slums of Mumbai to question the impact of the volatility of the market. And the turbulent times of an English village throughout the 20th century is the subject of Peter Moffat's latest television series. Producer: Katy Hickman. Show less